headline: Allstate Rides on Pricing Power & Protection Unit, But Risks Persist
summary: ALL leans on pricing power, premium growth and Protection Services momentum, while rising leverage and catastrophe losses keep risks in focus.

headline: 3 Reasons ALL is Risky and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Since July 2025, Allstate has been in a holding pattern, posting a small return of 0.9% while floating around $193.68. The stock also fell short of the S&P 500’s 8.2% gain during that period.
